1x <!--89-->Relentless Charge (stupid archers)    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">FOTR BLOCK<br />
IGNORE MY FELLOWSHIP:  i just whipped one together quickly to go with the shadow side. and yes, i am using three different aragorns.  Why? you ask. well, because i felt like it. its kinda interesting to draw two at once and have to decide which one will be more usefull.<br />
<br />
As for the shadow side, that&#39;s the one I care about. I&#39;ve thought about it carefully and tested it out a few times with decent success. (2 and 1)<br />
The main idea is to combo Otsea and the King as often as possible.  The beauty of this combo is putting 4 wounds on frodo regardless of what his fellowship is. The rest of the cards are either to help add burdens or to take advantage of the burdens. (dark whispers! this card is so much fun to surprise people with) The main problems of this deck are archery, burden removal, and choke.  For archery, i have a copy of relentless charge. also, most archers will lose skirmishes to the nazzies, so its not as much of a problem as it seems.  burden removal...  ummm...  i hope i add more than they can take away.  should i play with helpless?<br />
okay, choke: huge problem. the 2x Ring draws them and 3X morgul gates isn&#39;t always enough to play an 8 cost and 4 cost minion together.  oh well...<br />
<br />
So, what do you think? </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
